SIMPLE: torrefy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Torrefy
<hw>Tor"re*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Torrefied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Torrefying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>torrere</ets> to parch + <ets>-fy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>torr</ets>⟦eacute⟧<ets>fier</ets>, L.
<ets>torrefacere</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>torrify</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To dry by a fire.</def>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>To subject to scorching heat, so
as to drive off volatile ingredients; to roast, as ores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Pharm.)</fld> <def>To dry or parch, as drugs, on a
metallic plate till they are friable, or are reduced to the state
desired.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Torrens system</ent>⟦br⟧
